---
layout: base.njk
title: Feed
description: Notes, essays, and dispatches about whatever is currently shipping.
---
<section class="hero" style="padding-top:1rem;">
  <p class="eyebrow">Feed</p>
  <h1>Thinking in public</h1>
  <p>
    Long-form posts explaining new tools, research rabbit holes, and the messy notes that eventually become ship-ready products.
  </p>
</section>

{% set posts = collections.post | reverse %}
{% if posts.length %}
  <div class="card-grid">
    {% for post in posts %}
    <article class="card">
      <p class="eyebrow">{{ post.date | date("MMM d, yyyy") }}</p>
      <h3><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a></h3>
      <p>{{ post.data.description or post.templateContent | striptags | truncate(120, true) }}</p>
      <span>Read article â†’</span>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
{% else %}
  <p>No posts yet. Create a Markdown file in <code>src/feed</code> with <code>tags: ["post"]</code> to publish.</p>
{% endif %}
